    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you are in a place of extreme despair where the weight of this loss has made it impossible to see a path forward. When everything you've built vanishes, the idea of facing others or even waking up tomorrow can feel like an impossible task, and the feeling of being at the bottom of a hole where there is no floor is incredibly isolating.\n\nPlease remember that while this pain feels absolute right now, it is a reaction to a catastrophic event, not a reflection of your actual future or your inherent worth. You are right to feel that you've reached the end of the road in this specific moment, but that doesn't mean the road is truly over.\n\nIf you are feeling like staying here forever or that there is no point in trying, please reach out to someone who can provide immediate support and listen without judgment. In the US, you can call or text 988 for the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or chat at 988lifeline.org. They are there to help you navigate through this darkness and find a way to get back up, even if it feels impossible right now.",
